      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Tony Gualtieri" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Tony Gualtieri" href="/user/show/6970283-tony-gualtieri">Tony Gualtieri</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2244048911" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer15270302568260004499">This is the sort of book that gives a real insight to the Medieval mind. A cabinet of curiosities that illustrates the human penchant for creating certainty out of ignorance. One either loves this type of compendium or finds it tedious. I am firmly in the former camp.</span>

          </span>
        </div>


